Be very cautious with the 'mutation catalyst'; it can severely reduce an item's value and even make it negative. Only use it if you have a very low score and are willing to risk a complete reset, or if you're experimenting with an item you don't mind losing. Submit once you have a good score (25-30) to secure the round.

message: To get a reliable good score, always combine a 'lives on land' creature with a 'lives in the air' creature first. This consistently creates a hybrid with a value of 5. Immediately after, use the 'growth serum' on this new hybrid. This reliably increases its value to 15-25. Then, submit. I did not find a use for the mutation catalyst, but it might be worth experimenting with if you want to aim for values higher than what this strategy provides.
